dcterms:description: The ISPRS Potsdam Semantic Labeling dataset is comprised of 38 RGB tiles (6000 × 6000 px) and the associated IR and DSM images at 5cm spatial resolution. A comprehensive ground truth is provided for 24 tiles, which are used for semantic segmentation and vehicle detection.
dcterms:title: ISPRS Potsdam dataset

dcterms:creator: S. Razakarivony
F. Jurie
dcterms:description: The VEDAI dataset is comprised of 1268 RGB tiles (1024 × 1024px) and the associated IR image at 12.5cm spatial resolution. Annotations are provided detailing the position of the vehicles and the associated bounding box.
dcterms:title: VEDAI dataset

dcterms:description: The PASCAL VOC2012 dataset is a benchmark for object detection and segmentation tasks, providing a diverse set of images with annotated object classes.
dcterms:title: PASCAL VOC2012

dcterms:description: Microsoft COCO is a large-scale dataset designed for object detection, segmentation, and captioning, featuring images with complex scenes and multiple objects.
dcterms:title: Microsoft COCO

dcterms:description: The ISPRS Vaihingen Semantic Labeling dataset is used for urban object classification and 3D building reconstruction, providing high-resolution aerial images with semantic labels.
dcterms:title: ISPRS Vaihingen Semantic Labeling dataset
